The paper addresses the problem of action recognition in videos, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel compositional model for action recognition, which involves learning the structure of the model and optimizing its parameters (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of weakly supervised learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with multimedia understanding, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of contextual interactions and optimization of multi-layer parameters, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
